Andrea Pirlo has been fired as manager of Juventus on Friday. Juventus made the announcement in a statement via their Twitter handle on Friday morning. Pirlo took charge of Juventus last year, replacing Maurizio Sarri. Juventus are now expected to appoint a new manager ahead of next season. Meanwhile, Massimiliano Allegri has been linked with a return to the Serie A giants. Juventus finished in the fourth position on the Serie A table this season.